Then football collides to grab attention until the college bowl games and the Super Bowl.
During the COVID-19 interlude, these business models are being severely challenged.
With similar introspection, U.S. professional and collegiate sports can rethink their standards while revising their business models.
There is more focus today on safety of players, on developing better skills, and on how games are played.
With the right reforms now, sports can be even better than before, especially after this long reflection on its enduring purpose.